{
  "stem": "1799.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was something I grew up with, but somehow managed to deal with.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Brandenburg, less.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Even though there was antisemitism, I was usually-- I was, when I was on the street, I was either with friends or with more than myself, so that it wasn't just being-- they weren't able to single me out as an individual as easily as when I was, for instance, on vacation in that city that I described just now.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Most of my friends were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were all Jews, some of them from better known families in the city.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we also learned-- there were some that were my age, and we learned the preparation of the bar mitzvah together, more or less together.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was, particularly, one friend who I was very close with who was picked up, incidentally, in 1938, right after Crystal-- it was before Crystal Night-- when they picked up Eastern European Jews in Germany and brought them back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I had never seen him again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I heard that he survived, though.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father, because of his past in Germany-- meaning that he was a soldier in the first World War, an officer, and even had an Iron Cross, he was decorated, he had lost part of his hearing in one ear-- was known by the local authorities and was given quite a bit of authority to take care of Jews in need, and to help Jews emigrate.",
      "word_count": 66
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he did that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother and he often would discuss, why not leave ourselves?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When was this?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the mid '30s.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she had been eager at the time, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She saw the handwriting on the wall and urged him to consider leaving the country.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
